penalty shootout he left gresty road with one goal in five games and in october  joined andy ritchies second division oldham athletic in another onemonth spell he played six games for oldham scoring once against tranmere rovers in the football league trophy again with a header he spent two months on loan at alan littles halifax town from february  but remained goalless in his five games for the struggling third division club in november  he went out to swansea city on loan for the rest of the season brian flynns swans avoided relegation out of the football league by just a single point though richards managed a respectable tally of seven goals in  games he got his first league goal at vetch field on  november again with a header to wrap up a â€“ victory over shrewsbury town on  february he scored twice against cambridge united and also had a goal disallowed for offside he received his first sending off a week later after reacting badly to a foul by hartlepool united captain michael barron after discovering he was released from his contract at blackburn in april  richards aimed to sign with swansea permanently but instead signed a twoyear deal with northampton town northampton townedit though he scored twice at sixfields in the fa cup victory over nonleague westonsupermare it took  games before he bagged his first league goal for the cobblers the goal finally came on  february  in a â€“ win at darlington he then had one of the best games of his career on  march when he scored all four goals of the game against macclesfield town within the opening  minutes struggling with illness he scored in the playoff semifinals against mansfield town though his side crashed out on penalties he ended the â€“ campaign with  goals in  games his second season at sixfields was one blighted by injury picking up a knee injury in september  he had recovered by november but after making his return he ruptured his knee ligament keeping him out of action for a further three months in march  he was returning to fitness and so was loaned out to steve parkins rochdale to aid with his recovery after two goals in five games he returned to the cobblers finding out he had no future at northampton under colin calderwood he had a trial with bristol rovers before joining barnsley in august  barnsleyedit described as a young neil shipperley by manager andy ritchie his initial deal was shortterm so after fitting in well at the club he was offered an extension to his contract in december  in â€“ barnsley were promoted to the championship through the playoffs he started the playoff final victory over swansea city at the millennium stadium before being taken off for tommy wright after  minutes in total he played  of the tykes  league one games during the campaign and scored  goals in january  he was due to sign with port vale in partexchange for leon constantine however he remained at oakwell after the deal fell through he was released from his contract in may  despite making  appearances in the â€“ season port valeedit in june  richards joined port vale on a twoyear deal he was one of manager martin foyles last signings he became the club captain and quickly established himself as one of the clubs better players richards suffered with an ankle injury during the â€“ season he recovered towards the end of the season and began to find his goalscoring form once again though this was not enough to save lee sinnotts valiants from relegation out of league one at the end of the season the club were forced to accept a Â£ bid from cheltenham town due a release clause in his contract though chairman bill bratt rated him as a Â£ player turning down the chance of a move he instead signed a oneyear contract extension to keep him at vale park until the summer of  he went though a spell of injuries and suspensions during the â€“ season which caused him to miss almost twenty matches for dean glovers side an achilles injury picked up in late march kept him out of the team for the res