summer of  adams was confident richards would sign despite a lucrative offer from carlisle united and interest from numerous league one and scottish football league sides before the start of the â€“ season richards set himself a target of thirty goals he quickly established a deadly strike partnership with new teammate namesake justin richards sent off against burton albion at the start of january  more damaging to richards golden boot hopes and vales promotion ambitions was news that he would be sidelined for six weeks with muscle tear in his thigh with fraser and adams leaving the club new boss jim gannon handed richards the captaincy in february  on  february he marked his return from injury with a goal against aldershot town in a â€“ winÂ â€“ his first goal in three months on  march he scored his th career goal helping vale to beat lincoln city â€“ after hitting the twenty goal mark at the penultimate game of the season richards became the first vale player to score twenty goals for two seasons running since martin foyle the man who originally signed him for the club in â€“ and â€“ despite only turning  weeks before the start of the â€“ season the departure of namesake justin richards left him as the clubs most senior professional after scoring on the opening day against crawley town richards then spent a month on the sidelines with an ankle injury he made his return to the starting eleven against plymouth argyle on  september only to end up with a straight red card and three match ban for an incident with warren feeney an incident the striker described as handbags he returned to the first team on  october for only his fourth appearance of the campaign and bagged both of vales goals against rotherham united however after a further six games he was sidelined again due to a recurrence of his ankle injury and had to wait until december before he returned to action the injury required surgery to fully heal however richards chose to postpone the operation in order to try to help the valiants into an unlikely playoff spot despite the club entering administration in march richards refused the opportunity to jump ship to promotion hopefuls crawley town the administrators also rejected a loan offer from shrewsbury town he finished the season with  goals in  games thereby becoming the clubs top scorer for the fourth season in a row chesterfieldedit after weeks of speculation richards signed a twoyear deal with chesterfield in may  manager john sheridan and chief executive chris turner persuaded richards to make the switch to the league two side after a multitude of meetings with the player and a large increase in wages he had a poor start to the â€“ season as the spireites struggled to perform he also spent six weeks out injured with ankle troubles the clubs fortunes began to improve though after sheridan was sacked and replaced with paul cook richards also began to regain his form and scored five goals in his last five games to end the season on  goals in  appearances on  march  he played at wembley stadium after coming on as a substitute for sam hird in chesterfields â€“ defeat to peterborough united in the final of the football league trophy he scored a total of eight goals in  games as the spireites won promotion as divisional champions in â€“ return to northampton townedit richards playing for northampton town in  on  may  richards signed a threeyear contract with chris wilders northampton town after rejecting a new deal at chesterfield he said that he chose to stay in league two because i want to get as many promotions as i can before i hang my boots up he enjoyed an excellent start to the â€“ campaign going on a spell of seven goals in five games but was then sidelined with hamstring problems he scored  goals in  appearances to finish as the cobblers topscorer in the â€“ season despite having two months out with an achilles tear and was voted as the clubs player of the year northampton were promoted as champions in â€“ under manager chris wilder giving richards his second league two title in three years he finished as the clubs top scorer with  goals in  appearances despite missing the second half of the season after undergoing surgery to correct another achilles injury wilder stated that he believed richards would have scored  goals during the campaign if he had not been sidelined with injury richards was reported to have advised chairman kelvin thomas to appoint rob page as wilders successor as manager in may  he scored  goals in  appearances in the â€“ season and signed a new oneyear contract in may  after manager justin edinburgh described him as a captain a leader and someone who helps set the dressing room tone international careeredit he has been capped at england under and under levels he scored in an under international friendly against finland on  minutes after coming on as a substitute for arsenals john halls on  minutes style of playedit an accomplished set piece taker he is also a goalscorer from open play and can also hold the ball up well for his teammates in five years at port vale he scored  of his  penalties a success rate of  personal lifeedit richards has three children as of january  he describes himself as a laidback guy he won soccer ams crossbar challenge at vale park in  he raised Â£ for charity in november  career statisticsedit richards playing for port vale in  as of  may  club season division league fa cup efl cup other total apps goals apps goals apps goals apps goals apps goals crewe alexandra loan â€“ first division           oldham athletic loan â€“ second division       a a   halifax town loan â€“ third division           swansea city loan â€“ third division           blackburn rovers â€“ first division           â€“ premier league           â€“ premier league           total           rochdale loan â€“ league two           northampton town â€“ third division       ab b   â€“ league two       b    total           barnsley â€“ league one       ab    â€“ 